    <td valign="top"> 
      <p align="justify"><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Continental 
        Precision Instruments has more than 30 years experience as the master 
        U.S. manufacturer and supplier of practically any type of mechanical pressure 
        gauge. We&#146;re pioneers of gauge technology in pneumatics, refrigeration, 
        water service, utilities, medical, welding (oxygen cleaned per A.N.S.I. 
        B40.1) and many other fields. </font></p>
      <p align="justify"><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> We 
        also manufacture 11/2&quot;, 2&quot; and 21/2&quot; diameter bottom or 
        center back mounted dry type gauges beginning at 30&quot; vacuum and up 
        to 6000 psi to your specifications in our American factory.<br>
        <br>
        We will custom build to your individual specs at extremely competitive 
        pricing, utilizing our factory or our connections with the finest overseas 
        manufacturers. </font></p>
      <p align="justify"><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">We 
        stock economical, stainless steel cased Liquid Filled Gauges (up to 10,000 
        psi) that provide you with steady and accurate pressure readings or sensitive, 
        low pressure Diaphragm Capsule Gauges. Our latest round and square special 
        water pressure-temperature Tridicator Gauges with large easy-to-read dials 
        are ideal for hot water boiler systems.</font></p>
      <p align="justify"><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Continental 
        Precision Instruments has the global resources to help you meet your specific 
        pressure gauge requirements. Contact us today for more information or 
        to give us your lastest custom gauge specs.</font></p>
      <p align="justify"><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#000000">CPI's 
        <b><a href="gauges/utilityNPF1231.htm"><font color="#000000">NPF</font></a></b><a href="gauges/utilityNPF1231.htm"><font color="#000000">&reg;</font> 
        <b><font color="#000000">Utility</font></b></a> and <b><a href="gauges/npf_refrigeration1230.htm"><font color="#000000">Refrigeration 
        Gauges</font></a> </b>are built to last. Designed as a low cost alternative 
        for liquid filled gauges where pulsation is less than 15% of the full 
        scale. Available in 2&frac12;&quot; diameter bottom mount with plastic 
        case and polycarbonate lens. The <b>N</b>o <b>P</b>ointer <b>F</b>lutter&reg; 
        Gauges, featuring our exclusive encapsulated silicone dampened movement 
        system, provide steady and accurate pressure readings. The shock resistant 
        movement rarely needs re-calibration. These gauges are guaranteed not 
        to leak fluid or lose dampening characteristics. </font>
